AIM:
Perform the following Ansible actions:
a) Create and delete directories on managed node
b) Copy files to remote hosts using ad-hoc commands

--------------------------------------------------
Create Directory on Managed Node
--------------------------------------------------

ansible all -m file -a "path=/home/ubuntu/demo_dir state=directory"

--------------------------------------------------
Delete Directory on Managed Node
--------------------------------------------------

ansible all -m file -a "path=/home/ubuntu/demo_dir state=absent"

--------------------------------------------------
Create a Local File
--------------------------------------------------

echo "Hello from Ansible" > sample.txt

--------------------------------------------------
Copy File to Remote Hosts
--------------------------------------------------

ansible all -m copy -a "src=sample.txt dest=/home/ubuntu/sample.txt"

--------------------------------------------------
Verify File on Remote Host
--------------------------------------------------

ansible all -m shell -a "cat /home/ubuntu/sample.txt"

--------------------------------------------------
Expected Output
--------------------------------------------------

SUCCESS => {
    "changed": true,
    "msg": ""
}

--------------------------------------------------
RESULT
--------------------------------------------------

Successfully created and deleted directories on the managed node and copied files to remote hosts using Ansible ad-hoc commands.
